# Spike (dog)

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Jump to navigation Jump to search

    _For fictional dogs named Spike, see[Spike_(character)#Dogs](/wiki/Spike_\(character\)#Dogs "Spike \(character\)")_.
Spike [![Brian Keith The Westerner
1960.JPG](//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Brian_Keith_The_Westerner_1960.JPG/220px-
Brian_Keith_The_Westerner_1960.JPG)](/wiki/File:Brian_Keith_The_Westerner_1960.JPG)
Spike with [Brian Keith](/wiki/Brian_Keith "Brian Keith")  
---  
[Species](/wiki/Species "Species") | _[Canis lupus familiaris](/wiki/Dog "Dog")_  
[Breed](/wiki/Breed "Breed") | Mastador  
([Labrador Retriever](/wiki/Labrador_Retriever "Labrador
Retriever")/[Mastiff](/wiki/English_Mastiff "English Mastiff"))  
Sex | Male  
Nation from | [United States](/wiki/United_States "United States")  
Occupation | Dog actor  
Notable role | **King** in _[The She Creature](/wiki/The_She_Creature "The She Creature")_  
**Old Yeller** in _[Old Yeller](/wiki/Old_Yeller_\(film\) "Old Yeller
\(film\)")_  
**Patrasche** in _[A Dog of Flanders](/wiki/A_Dog_of_Flanders_\(1960_film\) "A
Dog of Flanders \(1960 film\)")_  
**Pete** in _[The Silent Call](/wiki/The_Silent_Call "The Silent Call")_  
Owner | [Frank Weatherwax](/wiki/Frank_Weatherwax "Frank Weatherwax")  
  
**Spike** was a lop-eared yellow
[Mastador](/w/index.php?title=Mastador&action=edit&redlink=1 "Mastador \(page
does not exist\)") ([Mastiff](/wiki/English_Mastiff "English
Mastiff")/[Labrador Retriever](/wiki/Labrador_Retriever "Labrador Retriever")
mix) and a dog actor best known for his performance as Old Yeller in the
[1957](/wiki/1957_in_film "1957 in film") [Disney film of the same
name](/wiki/Old_Yeller_\(film\) "Old Yeller \(film\)") co-starring [Tommy
Kirk](/wiki/Tommy_Kirk "Tommy Kirk"), [Dorothy McGuire](/wiki/Dorothy_McGuire
"Dorothy McGuire"), [Fess Parker](/wiki/Fess_Parker "Fess Parker"), and [Kevin
Corcoran](/wiki/Kevin_Corcoran "Kevin Corcoran"). Spike was rescued as a pup
from a shelter in [Van Nuys, California](/wiki/Van_Nuys,_California "Van Nuys,
California") and became the pet and pupil of animal trainer [Frank
Weatherwax](/wiki/Frank_Weatherwax "Frank Weatherwax").[1]

Spike also appeared as Patrasche in [20th Century Fox](/wiki/20th_Century_Fox
"20th Century Fox")'s _[A Dog of
Flanders](/wiki/A_Dog_of_Flanders_\(1960_film\) "A Dog of Flanders \(1960
film\)")_ with [Donald Crisp](/wiki/Donald_Crisp "Donald Crisp") and [David
Ladd](/wiki/David_Ladd "David Ladd") in [1959](/wiki/1959_in_film "1959 in
film") and as King in the [1956](/wiki/1956_in_film "1956 in film") film,
_[The She-Creature](/wiki/The_She_Creature "The She Creature")_. In 1961,
Spike was the star of _[The Silent Call](/wiki/The_Silent_Call "The Silent
Call")_ , playing as Pete with [Roger Mobley](/wiki/Roger_Mobley "Roger
Mobley"), [David McLean](/wiki/David_McLean_\(actor\) "David McLean
\(actor\)") and [Gail Russell](/wiki/Gail_Russell "Gail Russell"); the entire
movie focused on his efforts to reunite with his human family who had been
forced to leave him behind while traveling from Nevada to California.

Various television episodes of the period in which Spike appeared included
_[The Mickey Mouse Club](/wiki/The_Mickey_Mouse_Club "The Mickey Mouse Club")_
and _[Lassie](/wiki/Lassie_\(1954_TV_series\) "Lassie \(1954 TV series\)")_ ,
and he appeared in every episode of _[The
Westerner](/wiki/The_Westerner_\(TV_series\) "The Westerner \(TV series\)")_
with [Brian Keith](/wiki/Brian_Keith "Brian Keith").[2][3]
